data.text:
Let's Say Jack Kennedy Killed the Girl by William Crandell

ISBN: 9781734091861

Washington, July 1947. Young Congressman John F. Kennedy and private detective Jack Griffin form a tenuous friendship and rivalry at an Army-Navy Club dinner, hours before an eye-catching woman is murdered. A probable suspect, Kennedy hires Griffin to investigate, fearing the police will quickly arrest the "playboy congressman.
